&lt;li&gt;Hire and onboard: bring in the right profiles and get them productive quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold performance: track individual KPIs at every level, have honest conversations early, and support people to improve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the link between the team and leadership: surface what is working, flag what is not, and translate direction into daily habits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain HubSpot hygiene: ensure the team logs accurately so pipeline data can be trusted&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Account Executives to align outreach quality with closing requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience managing a sales team, ideally in a SaaS or tech environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native French speaker with strong written and verbal English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a coach first: you get energy from developing people, not from being the best seller in the room&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organisational skills - you can manage a small team across multiple roles without losing track of the detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable in a performance-oriented environment where targets are clear and accountability is real&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in hospitality tech, online travel, or B2B SaaS is an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
